{
  "stem": "10283.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Wasn't bad, but we had already shortages.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And I always said if it gets worse, they're not going to give food stamps or food to the Jews, and they're going to starve us to death.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And as long as my father made a living, he was not to be persuaded.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "He said, you're a young kid.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "You don't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And they wouldn't believe me.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was very scared.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I knew that this was going to end very badly.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I had-- I felt it in my gut, so to speak.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And when I came back from the Wolfratshausen, I didn't really have much to do.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I had-- couldn't go back to school, and it was not very nice.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] most of-- you know, most of all I remember that my parents then finally understood that they have to get out of Germany and that they have to find a country, which was very difficult.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I think Kristallnacht, yeah, and the camp.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Cousins came back from this concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I remember one cousin lived in the province in-- in [?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Brieg. ?] And [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] he came back from the concentration camp with the shaved hair and skinny and terribly upset.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so-- so we knew.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
